Package ohos.data.search.schema

Class CommonItem

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.data.search.model.IndexData
      • ohos.data.search.schema.Schema<CommonItem>
        • ohos.data.search.schema.CommonItem

  • public final class CommonItem
extends Schema<CommonItem>
    Represents the common index schema.

    The common index schema is used to develop basic search functions and applies to all common scenarios. It supports the following index fields: identifier, title, subtitle, name, alternateName, category, dateCreate, keywords, description, thumbnailUrl, url, potentialAction, reserved1, and reserved2. Among these fields, identifier is mandatory and can be set via the Schema.setIdentifier(java.lang.String) method. All other schemas will inherit this class, for example, ContactItem, MessageItem, DocumentItem, and EmailItem.

    Since:

    SystemCapability
